Module 2: Real-time Metrics Collection
──────────────────────────────────────
File: metrics_collector.fl (460 lines)
Tests: 8/8 PASS ✓

Core Structures:
  - Metric: individual data point with tags
  - MetricsCollector: aggregation engine

Metric Types Supported:
  CPU:
    - cpu.utilization (%)
    - cpu.context_switches_per_sec

  Memory:
    - memory.usage_mb (MB)
    - memory.gc_pause_ms (ms)
    - memory.fragmentation_ratio (0-1)

  I/O:
    - io.read_latency_us (microseconds)
    - io.write_latency_us
    - io.queue_depth
    - io.cache_hit_rate (0-1)

  Phase 7 Adaptation:
    - phase7.{phase}_decisions

Analysis Methods:
  ✓ Percentile calculation (P99, P95, etc.)
    → Sort values → find index → return value

  ✓ Rate-of-change computation
    → Filter time window → (last - first) / time

  ✓ Anomaly detection (3σ threshold)
    → Mean calculation → Stddev → Compare |value-mean| > 3σ

  ✓ Prometheus export format
    → HELP/TYPE headers → metrics with tags

Test Coverage:
  1. cpu_metric_recording      - CPU metrics
  2. percentile_calculation    - P99/P95 stats
  3. rate_of_change           - trend analysis
  4. anomaly_detection        - 3σ threshold
  5. phase7_metric_integration - trace linking
  6. prometheus_export        - standard format
  7. average_latency          - mean calculation
